{"in": {"title": "Questing Lores", "subtitle": "<span id=\"tr_lore_id\">Scene 2:</span>", "lines": ["TITLE: The Legend of Fangs, Scene 2", "NARRATOR: Fangs and Peony embark down a quiet forest trail. Snoozletown looms dimly in the distance.", "FANGS: (loud) So, can you tell me more about these Snoozlestones? What even are they?&nbsp;", "PEONY: Ever heard of the term \"inside voice\".", "FANGS: We are outside. Can you answer my question?", "PEONY: So much to learn (pause). Yes, I will tell you what I know of Snoozlestones.", "PEONY: Legend, has it that they are the creation of a genius, and the result of a bitter fight between two royal brothers.", "FANGS: This is how these kind of tales always begin.", "PEONY: The struggle for power is often the invisible hand behind many creations, what else can be said?", "PEONY: Anyways, legend has it that many centuries ago, a younger brother was left enraged when his elder inherited the throne of their father, who was the Duke of Snoozletown.&nbsp;", "PEONY: Seeking the throne, but well versed in the Machiavellian arts, the brother left Snoozletown, posing as an envoy, secretly seeking out a secret cult known for their practice of the mystic arts.", "NARRATOR: Fangs begins to wonder if all this hassle is really worth it. The mouse continues...", "PEONY: Using coin stolen from the royal bank, the younger brother purchased a recipe for a magical potion produced by the cult know as melatonite. Even a small dosage could induce a prolonged slumber.&nbsp;&nbsp;", "PEONY: Knowing that killing his brother would implicate himself as the main suspect, the brother instead used melatonite to synthesize the very first \"Snoozlestone\".", "FANGS: And did it work?", "PEONY: It did indeed, the younger brother slipped the Snoozlestone into his brother's dessert one evening, and the next morning the Duke did not awaken.", "NARRATOR: A faint hum of activity is now audible as Fangs and Peony near Snoozletown.&nbsp;", "PEONY: The younger brother was ecstatic. With his brother effectively in a coma, he could rule in his brother's stead temporarily. The power was his, while the crime remained anonymous.", "PEONY: But the dosage had been much too strong, and as decades passed and the elder brother's slumber continued, a guilt began to eat away at the mind of the younger brother(pause) ...insomnia ensued.", "PEONY: Seeking respite and rest, the younger brother reformulated his original Snoozlestone recipe, diluting the melatonite to a fraction of its former amount, and producing a new Snoozlestone designed to only last a night without the coma inducing effects of the first Snoozlestone. Thus the the modern Snoozlestone was born.&nbsp;", "FANGS: Wait, that's it? The younger brother just got away with his crime, the end?", "PEONY: What did you expect, the world is a brutal place. Anyways, there is not more time to digress. Snoozletown approaches, your human English is awful. Moral origins aside, Snoozlestones are suitable for your current predicament. They can be found heavily guarded in Snoozletown. Few know of their existence.", "FANGS: Fair enough, I need not concern myself with the follies of humans. I...", "PEONY: (whisper) Shh.. Something is coming.", "NARRATOR: Noises emmenate from the forest ahead.", "NARRATOR: Fangs insides knotted. He wished he had just eaten this foolish mouse.", "PEONY: (whisper) I know another way into Snoozletown, we'll have to go through the sewers.", "NARRATOR: Peony dashed into the thick bushes to the right of the trail. Fangs hesitated, but knowing he needed rest, put his instincts aside and followed Peony."], "speaker_map": {"NARRATOR": "Joanna", "TITLE": "Joanna", "Narrator": "Joanna", "Fangs": "Joanna", "PEONY": "Joanna", "FANGS": "Joanna", "SCENE": "Joanna"}}, "out": {"cache_id": "4c7204260a6c605e4d41d040f5a9b2dd", "audio_objects": [["2c92d3cee107cb65e45d51276c6d8bf6-the-legend-of-fangs--scen---", 0], ["83ef36ef657b109ecf781c7c46a4e4c8-fangs-and-peony-embark-do---", 0], ["2e05